  "elapsed_s": 186.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "The Talmud Torah was already a community institution, which, I suppose, was if not assisted financially, certainly supervised by the community and, to some extent, managed by the community, where you had what I-- could be considered regular grades where you advance from one class to the next, dependent on your [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] academic achievement.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I, I, I must enter here an the incident that occurred to me here maybe about five or six years ago.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "I had gone to Saint Terese to the [NON-ENGLISH], who, by the way, was a classmate of mine at one point.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And when I arrived there, up in the front of his synagogue, there was a man [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] arrayed in the usual Hasidic attire for the holidays, with a stramel and a [NON-ENGLISH] and a long beard fairly well-whitened already.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And someone came over to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And he said that that man up there wants to see me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "So I went up there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he, he turned to me-- after all that we have gone through, the Holocaust, almost 50 years of living in, in the United States or in North America.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And his first words out of his mouth were to me, tell me, when we went to Moshe Klein's Talmud Torah, did we study this tractate of the Talmud or that?",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am mentioning this because I think it really, quintessentially demonstrates a Jewish attachment to learning that is so deep-seated that after all that we have gone through, and after a separation and discontinuity of 45, 50 years, the first word out of a man who meets a former fellow student is, what tractate did we study?",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Everything else is forgotten.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Only the learning matters.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
